metadata.name: 1 - Untouched
metadata.description: Starved Rock State Park, Oglesby IL. This particular spot is a mostly "untouched" hidden gem above one of the main waterfalls. It's a long canyon with multiple falls trailing through until it reaches it's popular tourist destination. It's one of my favorite spots because it's tucked away from most, but rewards those adventurous enough to explore and look for it.
